Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, and cook for about 1 minute. Stir in chicken and saute until the surface of the chicken loses most of its pink color. Add the broccoli; stir to coat. Stir in orzo. Pour in the chicken stock and Ragu(R) Classic Alfredo Sauce. Stir well. Cover and reduce heat to medium. Cook until orzo is cooked, about 12 minutes. Turn off heat and uncover. Stir and allow to rest for 1 to 2 minutes before serving.